description.plain:
Benjamin Clarence Phillips Jr., better known by his stage name Autumn! or as TwinUzis, is an American recording artist and producer from Crowley, Louisiana. He currently resides in Houston, Texas.

Autumn! released his debut project, Happy Birthday, in June 2017 while working exclusively as a producer. His November 2018 mixtape, ##R3 ##R3, would gain traction on multiple platforms— particularly “Nina!” becoming one of his breakout songs. The Louisiana native would drop fourteen projects over three years, ending with September 2021’s Not Much Left.

On December 3, 2021, he released his highly anticipated single, “One Way!” The track’s leak was heavily pushed by TikTok, gaining the artist newfound, mainstream attraction. It would also appear on the artist’s major-label debut mixtape, Antagonist!

Some of his affiliates include the likes of Summrs, Lil Candypaint and Izaya Tiji among others. The Houston resident would also become close with the New York artist, Lil Tecca, who would feature on the remix of one of his most streamed songs, “Still The Same!”

songs.title: One Way!

description.plain:
“One Way!” is a track by Louisiana rapper and producer Autumn! on which the artist melodically reminisces on the troubles of a past relationship.

“One Way!” was first previewed in June 2021 via Instagram Live, becoming one of Autumn!’s most anticipated songs. He later played the song at a concert in November 2021.

The track is one of Autumn!’s most successful songs, amassing 2M Spotify streams in less than 48 hours since its release, reaching #12 on YouTube’s top trending list, and charting top 50 in 5+ countries.

songs.title: Still The Same!

description.plain:
“​Still The Same!” is the breakout single by the Louisiana native rapper, singer, producer, Autumn. On this song, Autumn addresses relationships, love over a melodic-struck trap beat that is self produced. The title of the song connects as an introduction to new fans, it’s self-explanatory.

The song was originally previewed on Autumn’s twitter January 4, 2020; And was eventually released to positive feedback.

“​Still The Same!” passed half a million streams on his SoundCloud, making it his first song ever to reach half a million streams that fast on that platform.

The song would also see success as it was remixed by another fellow artist Lil Tecca as well as just being a good song overall.

About 3 years after the song released, it appeared on the 2023 album Golden Child, Chapter 3, which also included a newer sequel track.

songs.title: You ˃ Them (Hate It!)

description.plain:
On “You > Them (Hate It!),” Autumn! raps about the trials and tribulations of a relationship he had over an up-tempo drum and bass beat.

This highly anticipated track was first previewed by Autumn! in a now-deleted Instagram post made on March 1, 2022.

Nearly two months following the initial preview, on April 14, 2022, Autumn! stated through his Instagram story that if his album Antagonist! reached top five on the charts, he’d release the song.

Later, on May 1, 2022—at his release concert for Antagonist!—Autumn! performed the full song, telling the crowd:

 I’m ready to drop that shit, not gon' lie
